<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    {{>upperlinks}}
    <title>Replit</title>
</head>

<body>
    {{>nav}}
    <div class="intro">
        <h1>AI-Powered Replit Overview</h1>
        <div class="read-word"></div>
        <div class="count-word"></div>
       <p>With Replit, developers can write, modify, and execute code directly from their browsers. Replit is a cloud-based
    development environment.
    Python, JavaScript, Ruby, Swift, and many other programming languages are supported by the platform.</p>
    <p>Replit's AI-powered autocompletion, which proposes code snippets and completes partially typed lines of code, is one of
    its standout features.
    In particular for young or unskilled programmers, this speeds up coding and reduces error-proneness.
    Replit's AI-powered syntax highlighting and indentation also contribute to better reading and comprehension of code.</p>
    <p>Replit also has collaboration capabilities that let numerous developers collaborate in real-time on the same codebase.
    For remote teams, as well as for students and teachers in educational contexts, this may be extremely helpful.</p>
    <p>Replit also interfaces with other programmes and platforms, such as Github, making it simple for programmers to exchange
    code and work together on projects.
    As a result, it serves as an excellent platform for both individual and team growth.</p>
    <p>Replit offers a user-friendly interface, a sizable developer community, and AI-powered capabilities in addition to other
    features.
    It is therefore a fantastic option for anyone searching for a practical, approachable, and potent development
    environment.</p>
    <p>Replit is an all-around effective and adaptable tool for developers, and its AI-powered capabilities set it apart from
    the competition in the competitive market for development environments.
    Replit is unquestionably a development platform worth taking into consideration, regardless of your level of experience.</p>
    </div>








    <script>
        const paragraphs = document.querySelectorAll(".intro p");
        const readTimeDiv = document.querySelector(".read-word");
        const count = document.querySelector(".count-word");

        const calculatedReadTime = () => {
            let numberOfWords = 0;
            const averageWPM = 265;

            paragraphs.forEach(paragraph => {
                numberOfWords += paragraph.innerHTML.split(" ").length;
            })

            let readTime = numberOfWords / averageWPM;

            readTimeDiv.innerHTML = Math.round(readTime) + " minute read"
            count.innerHTML = numberOfWords + " -words approximate"

        }
        calculatedReadTime();



    </script>

    {{>lowerlinks}}
</body>

</html>